Definition: Given a list of integers, keep only the integers that are not exactly divisible by 3. Return the resultant list even if it empty ("[]"). Note: Zero is divisible by 3.

Positive Examples.explanation: 532, 374, 71, 13 are kept in the output list because these are the only ones that are not exactly divisible by 3.
None of the values are not exactly divisible by 3. Hence, returned empty list as output.

Negative Examples.explanation: The output contains some integers that are divisible by 3.
The output only included one instance of the element 109 and 685, even though they appear two times each in the input list.
